(8/8) We are delivering #AffordableHealthcare for everyday Americans. Have questions? Contact us through our website: Thanedar.house.gov
(7/8) 2028-2029: Continued rollout of negotiated prices means more drug savings. We're committed to adding more medicines to this program annually.
(6/8) 2026-2027: Savings increase as previously negotiated drug price agreements are activated. Each year, we're working to ensure affordable rates for even more medications.
(5/8) 2025: Out-of-pocket expenses for drugs are capped at $2,000. A new discount program is also introduced, ensuring more savings on medicines.
(4/8) 2024: Under Medicare, those who reach the "catastrophic phase" won't face high drug charges. Mechanisms are in place to prevent unexpected drug plan rate increases.
(3/8) 2023: Good news for Medicare enrollees‚Äîinsulin costs are capped at $35/month. Additionally, coverage expands to include key adult vaccines, like the one for shingles.
(2/8) 2022: Those with ACA health plans saw more savings. Medicare increased support for specific affordable drug alternatives, promoting competition and lowering costs.
